netiTrunkMIB.name: netiTrunkMIB

revisions.description: Extended draft. This revision is preliminary. Read-write objects have been added to give full managablity to the interfaces in the DPP-IP group. Values that limits the configuration of the local DPP-IP interfaces have been introduced in the dppipLimitsTable. Similarly, limits of the peer DPP-IP interfaces have been added in the dppipPeerLimitsTable.
Extended draft. This revision is preliminary. The dppipDelayVar01 object has been added to dppipEntry. All objects in the MIB are read-only.
Extended draft. This revision is preliminary. More objects have been added to dppipEntry to make the configuration information and status more complete. All objects in the MIB are read-only.
Draft. This revision is preliminary. Future revisions are likely to be incompatible with this revision.

netiTrunkMIB.contactinfo: Net Insight AB Box 42093 SE-126 14 Stockholm Sweden Tel +46-8-685 0400 info@netinsight.se
netiTrunkMIB.description: MIB for DTM network links (trunks). DTM trunks provide transport of DTM data between two DTM networks nodes. The MIB currently includes the DPP-IP group (neti-dppip), providing management of DPP-IP encapsulated DTM over IP/Ethernet. It includes configuration information and status.

FecMode.name: FecMode
FecMode.description: The mode of operation of the Forward Error Correction function (FEC). The FEC function may be not used (fecNone), used for column correction (fec1D) or used for both row and column correction (fec2D).

DppipSupport.name: DppipSupport
DppipSupport.description: Represents the support of a specific DPP-IP function: octet contents 1 major version 2 minor version Any minor version N.x includes support for any minor version M.y with major version M<N. Minor version N.n includes support for any minor version N.m with the same major version N and m<n.

dppipNumber.name: dppipNumber
dppipNumber.description: The number of DPP-IP interfaces (regardless of their current state) present on this system.

dppipLastChange.name: dppipLastChange
dppipLastChange.description: The value of sysUpTime when status or configuration of any the objects in the dppipTable was last changed.

dppipTable.name: dppipTable
dppipTable.description: A list of DPP-IP interface entries. The number of entries is given by the value of dppipNumber. The following objects need to be written simultaneously, i.e. as a single write operation, while dppipAdminStatus is `up': dppipTxSlots, dppipMtu, dppipTxFecMode, dppipTxFecRows, dppipTxFecCols

dppipEntry.name: dppipEntry
dppipEntry.description: A DPP-IP interface entry containing objects at the subnetwork layer and below for a particular interface.

dppipIndex.name: dppipIndex
dppipIndex.description: A value greater than zero that is unique for each DPP-IP interface. The value for each DPP-IP interface must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re-initialization.

dppipName.name: dppipName
dppipName.description: The textual name of the interface. The value of this object should be the name of the DPP-IP interface as assigned by the local device.

dppipAddress.name: dppipAddress
dppipAddress.description: The IPv4 address of the DPP-IP interface.

dppipNetMask.name: dppipNetMask
dppipNetMask.description: The subnet mask associated with the IP address of DPP-IP interface. The value of the mask is an IP address with all the network bits set to 1 and all the hosts bits set to 0.

dppipDefaultGateway.name: dppipDefaultGateway
dppipDefaultGateway.description: The IPv4 address of the default gateway. Packets addressed to a destination outside the subnet of the DPP-IP interface are by default routed to this gateway.

dppipPeerAddress.name: dppipPeerAddress
dppipPeerAddress.description: The IPv4 address of the peer DPP-IP interface at the remote end of the DTM trunk.

dppipTxSlots.name: dppipTxSlots
dppipTxSlots.description: The DPP-IP interface's current transmit side capacity in slots per DTM frame.

dppipTxUsedCapacity.name: dppipTxUsedCapacity
dppipTxUsedCapacity.description: An estimate of the transmit side physical layer capacity used by the DPP-IP interface in bits per second. It represents a minimum required capacity along the network path.

dppipRxSlots.name: dppipRxSlots
dppipRxSlots.description: The DPP-IP interface's current receive side capacity in slots per DTM frame.

dppipRxUsedCapacity.name: dppipRxUsedCapacity
dppipRxUsedCapacity.description: An estimate of the receive side physical layer capacity used by the DPP-IP interface in bits per second. It represents a minimum required capacity along the network path.

dppipDelayVariation.name: dppipDelayVariation
dppipDelayVariation.description: The RMS (i.e. standard deviation) value of the DPP-IP path delay variation in ns. This value represents a momentary snapshot of the delay variation.

dppipOperStatus.name: dppipOperStatus
dppipOperStatus.description: The current operational state of the interface. The testing(3) state indicates that no operational frames can be passed.

dppipFailure.name: dppipFailure
dppipFailure.description: A textual string describing a fault status on the DPP-IP interface. The object presents an empty string if there are no faults on the interface.

dppipReceivedFrames.name: dppipReceivedFrames
dppipReceivedFrames.description: The total number of DPP-IP frames that have been received.

dppipMissingFrames.name: dppipMissingFrames
dppipMissingFrames.description: The number of DPP-IP frames that were missing in the frame sequence, i.e. the expected sequence numbers were not found in the DPP-IP framing buffer.

dppipDeliveredFrames.name: dppipDeliveredFrames
dppipDeliveredFrames.description: The total number of DPP-IP data frames that have been delivered to the DTM interface.

dppipDroppedFrames.name: dppipDroppedFrames
dppipDroppedFrames.description: The number of DPP-IP frames that have been received and have not been processed since the interface was unable to align them to the DPP-IP frame sequence.

dppipDuplicateFrames.name: dppipDuplicateFrames
dppipDuplicateFrames.description: The number of DPP-IP frames that were received with a sequence number of an already processed DPP-IP frame.

dppipReorderedFrames.name: dppipReorderedFrames
dppipReorderedFrames.description: The number of DPP-IP frames that were received out of order, but could still be aligned to the DPP-IP frame sequence.

dppipLostFrames.name: dppipLostFrames
dppipLostFrames.description: The number of missing DPP-IP data frames that could not be delivered to the DTM interface.

dppipRecoveredFrames.name: dppipRecoveredFrames
dppipRecoveredFrames.description: The number of missing DPP-IP data frames that were recovered by the FEC procedure.

dppipSentFrames.name: dppipSentFrames
dppipSentFrames.description: The total number of DPP-IP frames that have been sent.

dppipDelayVarPtp.name: dppipDelayVarPtp
dppipDelayVarPtp.description: The point-to-point value of the DPP-IP path delay variation in nanoseconds. The special value 0 means that the measurement is incomplete

dppipDelayVar999.name: dppipDelayVar999
dppipDelayVar999.description: The 99.9 percentile value of the DPP-IP path delay variation given in nanoseconds. The special value 0 means that the measurement is incomplete.

dppipAdminStatus.name: dppipAdminStatus
dppipAdminStatus.description: The desired state of the interface.

dppipVlan.name: dppipVlan
dppipVlan.description: The VLAN identity associated to the DPP-IP interface. The value 0 indicates that the DPP-IP interface does not belong to a VLAN. The value -1 indicates that Ethernet frames from the DPP-IP interface are not tagged.

dppipDelayVar01.name: dppipDelayVar01
dppipDelayVar01.description: The 0.1 percentile value of the DPP-IP path delay variation given in nanoseconds. The special value 0 means that the measurement is incomplete.

dppipPrio.name: dppipPrio
dppipPrio.description: The Ethernet priority for frames sent from the DPP-IP interface. Ignored if frames are untagged (i.e. dppipVlan is -1).

dppipPhysIf.name: dppipPhysIf
dppipPhysIf.description: A reference to an object representing the physical interface that supports the DPP-IP interface. The special value .0.0 is used, when no such reference is available.

dppipMtu.name: dppipMtu
dppipMtu.description: The Maximum Transmission Unit of the DPP-IP interface, i.e. the maximum size of the DPP-IP payload, including IP header, UDP header and DPP-IP header.

dppipTtl.name: dppipTtl
dppipTtl.description: The Time To Live of frames sent at the DPP-IP interface. This value is set in the IP header.

dppipDscp.name: dppipDscp
dppipDscp.description: The Differential Services Coding Point of frames sent at the DPP-IP interface. This value is set in the IP header.

dppipRxSlotsPerFrame.name: dppipRxSlotsPerFrame
dppipRxSlotsPerFrame.description: Number of DTM slots per received DPP-IP data frame.

dppipAvailTxSlots.name: dppipAvailTxSlots
dppipAvailTxSlots.description: The maximum transmit slot rate (slots/frame) that can be allocated at the DTM switch.

dppipAvailRxSlots.name: dppipAvailRxSlots
dppipAvailRxSlots.description: The maximum receive slot rate (slots/frame) that can be allocated at the DTM switch.

dppipMinUsageRatio.name: dppipMinUsageRatio
dppipMinUsageRatio.description: The minimum allowed usage ratio (used slots/configured slots) in per-mille, when dynamic trunk functionality is used. 1000 is default and indicates that the Dynamic Trunk function is disabled. Requires Dynamic Trunk function support equal to 1.1 or higher.

dppipTxTranspSlots.name: dppipTxTranspSlots
dppipTxTranspSlots.description: The DPP-IP interface's current transmit side capacity in slots per DTM frame that is actually transported over the. When Dynamic Trunk functionality is disabled this is equal to dppipTxSlots. When Dynamic Trunk functionality is enabled this is less or equal to dppipTxSlots, since slots that are not used by any channel need not be transported. Requires Dynamic Trunk function support equal to 1.1 or higher.

dppipRxTranspSlots.name: dppipRxTranspSlots
dppipRxTranspSlots.description: The DPP-IP interface's current receive side capacity in slots per DTM frame that is actually transported. When Dynamic Trunk functionality is disabled this is equal to dppipRxSlots. When Dynamic Trunk functionality is enabled this is less or equal to dppipRxSlots, since slots that are not used by any channel need not be transported. Requires Dynamic Trunk function support equal to 1.1 or higher.

dppipNomDTDelay.name: dppipNomDTDelay
dppipNomDTDelay.description: The nominal extra delay in ns when the Dynamic Trunk function is enabled. Requires Dynamic Trunk function support equal to 1.1 or higher.

dppipTxFecMode.name: dppipTxFecMode
dppipTxFecMode.description: The DPP-IP interface's current mode of operation of the transmit side Forward Error Correction function (FEC). The FEC function may be not used (fecNone), used for column correction (fec1D) or used for both row and column correction (fec2D).

dppipTxFecRows.name: dppipTxFecRows
dppipTxFecRows.description: The DPP-IP interface's current number of data rows in the transmit side Forward Error Correction (FEC) matrix. This object is not applicable when dppipTxFecMode is fecNone.

dppipTxFecCols.name: dppipTxFecCols
dppipTxFecCols.description: The DPP-IP interface's current number of data columns in the transmit side Forward Error Correction (FEC) matrix. This object is not applicable when dppipTxFecMode is fecNone.

dppipRxFecMode.name: dppipRxFecMode
dppipRxFecMode.description: The DPP-IP interface's current mode of operation of the receive side Forward Error Correction function (FEC). The FEC function may be not used (fecNone), used for column correction (fec1D) or used for both row and column correction (fec2D).

dppipRxFecRows.name: dppipRxFecRows
dppipRxFecRows.description: The DPP-IP interface's current number of data rows in the receive side Forward Error Correction (FEC) matrix. This object is not applicable when dppipRxFecMode is fecNone.

dppipRxFecCols.name: dppipRxFecCols
dppipRxFecCols.description: The DPP-IP interface's current number of data columns in the receive side Forward Error Correction (FEC) matrix. This object is not applicable when dppipRxFecMode is fecNone.

dppipCntControl.name: dppipCntControl
dppipCntControl.description: Controls the statistics counter monitoring. The statistics monitoring is restarted and all counters set to 0, by writing `reset' to this object.

dppipSuppressAlarms.name: dppipSuppressAlarms
dppipSuppressAlarms.description: Suppression control for alarms from the DPP-IP interface. When set to `true', all alarms are suppressed.

dppipSigFailFilter.name: dppipSigFailFilter
dppipSigFailFilter.description: Signal fail filter hold-off time in milliseconds. Trail Signal Fail conditions must be persistent during the hold-off time, before operStatus is changed from `up' to `down'.

dppipDegThreshold.name: dppipDegThreshold
dppipDegThreshold.description: The detection threshold for DEG alarm. A bad second is declared when the number of errored blocks is equal to or greater than the threshold, otherwise a good second is declared. Default is 1200

dppipDegPeriod.name: dppipDegPeriod
dppipDegPeriod.description: The persistence time for detection of DEG alarm as the number of consecutive seconds with changed status (bad or good) before the alarm is set or cleared.

dppipTolJitter.name: dppipTolJitter
dppipTolJitter.description: The tolerated jitter and wander of the DPP-IP interface given in microseconds.

dppipLimitsTable.name: dppipLimitsTable
dppipLimitsTable.description: A list of DPP-IP interface limits entries. The number of entries is given by the value of dppipNumber.

dppipLimitsEntry.name: dppipLimitsEntry
dppipLimitsEntry.description: A DPP-IP interface limits entry containing limits for a particular interface.

dppipMaxFecMode.name: dppipMaxFecMode
dppipMaxFecMode.description: The DPP-IP interface's maximum mode of operation of the Forward Error Correction function (FEC). The FEC function may be not used (fecNone), used for column correction (fec1D) or used for both row and column correction (fec2D).

dppipMaxFecRows.name: dppipMaxFecRows
dppipMaxFecRows.description: The DPP-IP interface's maximum number of data rows in the transmit side Forward Error Correction (FEC) matrix.

dppipMinFecRows.name: dppipMinFecRows
dppipMinFecRows.description: The DPP-IP interface's minimum number of data rows in the transmit side Forward Error Correction (FEC) matrix.

dppipMaxFecCols.name: dppipMaxFecCols
dppipMaxFecCols.description: The DPP-IP interface's maximum number of data columns in the transmit side Forward Error Correction (FEC) matrix.

dppipMinFecCols.name: dppipMinFecCols
dppipMinFecCols.description: The DPP-IP interface's minimum number of data columns in the transmit side Forward Error Correction (FEC) matrix.

dppipMaxFecElems.name: dppipMaxFecElems
dppipMaxFecElems.description: The DPP-IP interface's maximum number of data elements in the transmit side Forward Error Correction (FEC) matrix.

dppipMaxTxSlots.name: dppipMaxTxSlots
dppipMaxTxSlots.description: The maximum number of slots per DTM frame that can be allocated at the DPP-IP transmit interface.

dppipMinTxSlots.name: dppipMinTxSlots
dppipMinTxSlots.description: The minimum number of slots per DTM frame that can be allocated at the DPP-IP transmit interface.

dppipMaxTolJitter.name: dppipMaxTolJitter
dppipMaxTolJitter.description: The maximum tolerated jitter that can be configured expressed in units of DPP-IP inter-frame intervals. The DPP-IP inter-frame interval in microseconds is: dppipRxSlotsPerFrame * 125 / dppipRxSlots.

dppipMinTolJitter.name: dppipMinTolJitter
dppipMinTolJitter.description: The minimum tolerated jitter that can be configured expressed in units of DPP-IP inter-frame intervals. The DPP-IP inter-frame interval in microseconds is: dppipRxSlotsPerFrame * 125 / dppipRxSlots.

dppipDTSupport.name: dppipDTSupport
dppipDTSupport.description: The local interface's maximum level of support for the Dynamic Trunk function.

dppipTTSupport.name: dppipTTSupport
dppipTTSupport.description: The local interface's maximum level of support for the Time Transfer function.

dppipPeerLimitsTable.name: dppipPeerLimitsTable
dppipPeerLimitsTable.description: A list of DPP-IP interface limits entries. The number of entries is given by the value of dppipNumber.

dppipPeerLimitsEntry.name: dppipPeerLimitsEntry
dppipPeerLimitsEntry.description: A DPP-IP interface peer limits entry containing limits for the peer of a particular interface.

dppipPeerMaxFecMode.name: dppipPeerMaxFecMode
dppipPeerMaxFecMode.description: The peer interface's maximum mode of operation of the Forward Error Correction function (FEC). The FEC function may be not used (fecNone), used for column correction (fec1D) or used for both row and column correction (fec2D).

dppipPeerMaxFecRows.name: dppipPeerMaxFecRows
dppipPeerMaxFecRows.description: The peer interface's maximum number of data rows in the receive side Forward Error Correction (FEC) matrix.

dppipPeerMinFecRows.name: dppipPeerMinFecRows
dppipPeerMinFecRows.description: The peer interface's minimum number of data rows in the receive side Forward Error Correction (FEC) matrix.

dppipPeerMaxFecCols.name: dppipPeerMaxFecCols
dppipPeerMaxFecCols.description: The peer interface's maximum number of data columns in the receive side Forward Error Correction (FEC) matrix.

dppipPeerMinFecCols.name: dppipPeerMinFecCols
dppipPeerMinFecCols.description: The peer interface's minimum number of data columns in the receive side Forward Error Correction (FEC) matrix.

dppipPeerMaxFecElems.name: dppipPeerMaxFecElems
dppipPeerMaxFecElems.description: The peer interface's maximum number of data elements in the receive side Forward Error Correction (FEC) matrix.

dppipPeerMaxRxSlots.name: dppipPeerMaxRxSlots
dppipPeerMaxRxSlots.description: The maximum number of slots per DTM frame that can be allocated at the receive interface in the peer.

dppipPeerMinRxSlots.name: dppipPeerMinRxSlots
dppipPeerMinRxSlots.description: The minimum number of slots per DTM frame that can be allocated at the DPP-IP receive interface of the peer.

dppipPeerDTSupport.name: dppipPeerDTSupport
dppipPeerDTSupport.description: The peer interface's maximum level of support for the Dynamic Trunk function.

dppipPeerTTSupport.name: dppipPeerTTSupport
dppipPeerTTSupport.description: The peer interface's maximum level of support for the Time Transfer function.
